_json.gridTitle: TRUTH REMAINS - “There should be a parallel between our supplications and our thanksgivings. We ought not to leap in prayer, and limp in praise.” - Charles Spurgeon | Facebook
_json.description: Charles Haddon (CH) Spurgeon (19 June 1834 – 31 January 1892) was a British Particular Baptist preacher. Spurgeon remains highly influential among Christians of various denominations, among whom he is known as the "Prince of Preachers". He was a strong figure in the Reformed Baptist tradition. Spurgeon produced powerful sermons of penetrating thought and precise exposition. Many Christians have discovered Spurgeon's messages to be among the best in Christian literature.
